<h1 style='margin-top:24px;'>Cartoonist</h1>
<table class="badges" style='padding:2em;'>
<tr>
<td>
<p>
Your job here is to create a short animated movie, similar to many
around the web. It doesn't need to be too long (1min is fine). The
major requisite is that there must a story with a beginning, middle
and end. You can do it with your own story or remake an existing one,
or even a cartoon version of some real-life thing. You can do it using
any technology you want. Here is a contribution from a few years ago, by João Amaral: 
</p>


<iframe width="560" height="315"
	src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/lXb3LdXs1o4" frameborder="0"
	allowfullscreen></iframe>


<p>Important: you must create the animation yourself. The use of tools such as <a href="http://www.synfig.org/">Synfig</a> or <a href="http://www.pencil2d.org/">Pencil2D</a> is ok. The use of tools where you just "direct" the characters in a limited array of possibilities such as <a href="https://www.powtoon.com/">PowToon</a> is not! Design your own characters, animate them, and tell an interesting story! You can even do it by hand, like the great Terry Gilliam shows you, below:
</p>

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xs7WaL44_Iw" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>

<p>
Post a description of the techniques and tools you used to create the
  video, the script and, of course, the resulting video. Be original,
  tasteful, and, as always, we may ask for improvements/changes before
  accepting the result, especially if the quality or originality
  requirements aren't met.
</p>

</ul>



